31/01/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Hina Jilani, Special Representative of the UN Secretary General on Human Rights Defenders, expressed her concern over violations of media freedom in Macedonia and cases involving police action against journalists. 
She made her statement after wrapping up a three-day visit to the country. 
Jilani said she had received the Macedonian government's assurance that it would do its best to promote human rights in all institutions related to this issue. 
(Makfax - 30/01/03)
